<subSubSection lastPageId="75" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="74.[151,533,1804,1831]" box="[151,533,1804,1831]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,533,1804,1831]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" reason="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,533,1804,1831]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[151,452,1804,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulphureipes">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,452,1804,1831]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Pamphilius sulphureipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="74.[151,1436,1877,2011]" lastBlockId="75.[151,1437,151,645]" lastPageId="75" lastPageNumber="76" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
The members of this species group are characterized as follows: upper part of head glabrous; facial crest in male very strongly swollen, bluntly carinate; antennal flagellomere 2 1.8–2.9 × length of flagellomere 1; right mandible tridentate but incision between middle and apical teeth shallow or bidentate with only basal shoulder to apical tooth; left mandible tridentate with low middle tooth; wings hyaline; forewing with cell C glabrous or pilose; femora entirely pale. Subgenital plate in male without large setose appendage. Ovipositor sheath appendage slender subconical, pilose. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[452,560,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 70" captionStartId="159.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@159.[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="159" captionText="FIGURE 70. Pamphilius coreanus, male, Korea – (a) dorsally, (b) lateroventrally, (c) head &amp; thorax dorsally, (d) head &amp; thorax ventrolaterally, (e) face, (f) antenna, (g) claw, (h) genitalia dorsally." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876676" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876676/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Figs. 70h</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[570,628,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 120" captionStartId="209.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@209.[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="209" captionText="FIGURE 120. Pamphilius sulphureipes sulphureipes, male, Korea – (a) dorsally, (b) lateroventrally, (c) head &amp; thorax dorsally, (d) head &amp; thorax ventrolaterally, (e) face, (f) antenna, (g) genitalia dorsally, (h) claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876793" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876793/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<quantity box="[570,628,187,213]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.2" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" unit="g" value="120.0">120g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[640,727,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 136" captionStartId="225.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@225.[151,1435,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="225" captionText="FIGURE 136. Pamphilius zhelochovtsevi, male, Korea – (a) dorsally, (b) lateroventrally, (c) head &amp; thorax dorsally, (d) head &amp; thorax ventrolaterally, (e) face, (f) antenna, (g) genitalia dorsally, (h) genitalia ventrally, (i) claw." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876833" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876833/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
<quantity box="[640,698,187,213]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.3599999999999999" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" unit="g" value="136.0">136g</quantity>
, h
</figureCitation>
): proximal ventral arm of gonostipes normal; apiceps narrow or broad; valviceps in lateral view rather short, apex directed upwards, ventral margin more or less rounded, without conspicuous dorsoapical process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="75" pageNumber="76" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
Five East Asian species, two represented by two subspecies, are included (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1060,1260,295,321]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
). Three species have been recorded in the Russian Far East and 
<collectingCountry box="[689,761,331,357]" name="South Korea" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Korea</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
Twenty sequences of four species were treated in the COI analysis and nine sequences of three species in the NaK analysis. In both analyses (
<figureCitation box="[508,608,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 144" captionStartId="231.[151,250,1187,1211]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,187,1159]" captionTargetId="figure-19@231.[151,1436,181,1163]" captionTargetPageId="231" captionText="FIGURE 144. Condensed ML tree based on CO1 gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius sulphureipes group." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876849/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Figs 144</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[619,664,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 158" captionStartId="243.[151,250,886,910]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,185,858]" captionTargetId="figure-19@243.[151,1436,181,862]" captionTargetPageId="243" captionText="FIGURE 158. Condensed ML tree based on NaK gene sequences, with details of Pamphilius sulphureipes group." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6876880" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6876880/files/figure.png" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">158</figureCitation>
), the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[724,892,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulphureipes">
<emphasis box="[724,892,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">P. sulphureipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group was retrieved as monophyletic with 100% UFBoot value. In both trees, the relationship (( 
<taxonomicName box="[687,818,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coreanus">
<emphasis box="[687,818,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">P. coreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
+ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[850,1021,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulphureipes">
<emphasis box="[850,1021,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">P. sulphureipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) + 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benes" authorityYear="1974" box="[1064,1256,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhelochovtsevi">
<emphasis box="[1064,1256,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">P. zhelochovtsevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) was supported by 99 or 100% UFBoot value on each node, and in the COI analysis, an additional species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Shinohara, 1979" authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1979" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ishikawai">
<emphasis box="[1174,1308,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">P. ishikawai</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="151 - 161" refId="ref75920" refString="Shinohara, A. (1979) A study of the sulphureipes complex of the genus Pamphilius (Hymenoptera: Pamphiliidae). Transactions of the Shikoku Entomological Society, 14, 151 - 161." type="journal article" year="1979">Shinohara, 1979</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[283,350,511,537]" name="Japan" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Japan</collectingCountry>
, was recovered as sister to the clade of the three species, again with 100% UFBoot support.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="75.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">
A host plant is known only for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1979" box="[560,696,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ishikawai">
<emphasis box="[560,696,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">P. ishikawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whose larvae are solitary leaf-rollers on 
<taxonomicName box="[1174,1331,547,573]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Saxifragaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1349,1427,547,573]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Astilbe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1349,1427,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">Astilbe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Kameda, Y. &amp; Ibuki, S. &amp; Kiyoshi, T. &amp; Kakuda, T. &amp; Kojima, H." box="[159,422,583,609]" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" pagination="167 - 178" refId="ref78036" refString="Shinohara, A., Kameda, Y., Ibuki, S., Kiyoshi, T., Kakuda, T. &amp; Kojima, H. (2016 a) Pamphilius ishikawai feeds on Astilbe: the first record of Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera) associated with Saxifragaceae. Zootaxa, 4098 (1), 167 - 178. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4098.1.8" type="journal article" year="2016">
Shinohara 
<emphasis box="[282,340,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="75" pageNumber="76">et al.</emphasis>
2016a
</bibRefCitation>
). The other four members of this species group may also be associated with the plants of 
<taxonomicName box="[151,312,619,645]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="75" pageNumber="76" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Saxifragaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
